author: The Current
description:
Watch Palmyra’s impromptu outdoor performance of “Arizona” 
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

On a beautiful summer day in the southern Minnesota city of Rochester, Virginia trio Palmyra performed their song “Arizona” outside Thesis Beer Project just ahead of The Current’s Happy Hour event on September 4, 2025. Watch the performance above.

Musicians
Mānoa Bell – bass
Teddy Chipouras – guitar, vocals
Sasha Landon – mandolin, vocals

author: The Current
description:
Yam Haus play “One Bullet Left” at Milk & Honey Ciders
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Just before playing a full set at The Current’s Happy Hour event on August 7, 2025, at Milk & Honey Cider in the central Minnesota town of St. Joseph, Yam Haus performed this impromptu, acoustic version of their song, “One Bullet Left.” Watch their performance above.

Musicians
Lars Pruitt – vocals, guitar
Zach Beinlich – backing vocals
Jake Felstow – percussion, backing vocals

To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of Static Panic, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited The Current studio back in 2018.
